  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients in critical illness frequently present hypermetabolism， which can extremely
      increase the rest energy expenditure（REE）. We hypothesize that if we alleviate the extremely
      increased REE will improve ICU patients' outcome
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study focuses on the early changes of REE of critical ill patients when they admitted
      to ICU.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
